# Coding Style (Roblox Luau)

## String interpolation

- Use Roblox backtick interpolation; do not use `string.format`.
- Syntax: place expressions inside `{}` within a backtick string.

```lua
-- Good
TextLabel.Text = `Cutting Power: {args.power}`

local playerName = player.Name
local coins = 42
local message = `{playerName} found {coins} coins!`

-- Avoid
-- local message = string.format("%s found %d coins!", playerName, coins)
```

## Defensive programming

- Do not over-do defensive programming. When resources and config are present and callers follow the contract, omit redundant nil checks, fallbacks, and warns so that issues surface during development or testing.

## Code blocks

- Do not use `do end` blocks.
- Use function scoping or other control structures instead.

```lua
-- Good
local function processData()
	local result = calculate()
	return result
end

-- Avoid
-- do
--     local result = calculate()
--     return result
-- end
```
